LAGOS – The African Regional Organisation of the International Trade Union Confederation (ITUC-Africa), has invited the immediate past President of the Nigeria Labour Congress (NLC), Comrade Ayuba Wabba to the 5th Ordinary Congress of the Congress scheduled for Nairobi, Kenya In a statement signed by the ITUC-Africa’s President is Mody Guiro and General Secretary Kwasi Adu-Amankwah, comrade Wabba is specially invited for the Congress scheduled for 28 – 30 November 2023 in Nairobi under the central theme: “AMKA, Africa”, to appreciate him for his contributions to the growth, strength, and progress of our organisation. The African Regional Organisation of the International Trade Union Confederation (ITUC-Africa) is a pan-African trade union organisation created in November 2007 following the merger of two former African trade union organisations, namely ICFTU-Afro and DOAWTU. ITUC-Africa has 17 million declared members and 101 affiliated trade union centres in 51 African countries. The headquarters of ITUC-Africa is now in Lome, Togo. Part of the statement read: “We are pleased to invite you to the 5th Ordinary Congress of the ITUC-Africa scheduled for 28 – 30 November 2023 in Nairobi , Kenya under the central theme: “AMKA, Africa!”. “This is an invitation to an award during the Congress, in recognition of your important and appreciative contributions to the growth, strength, and progress of our organisation. “The Congress will be preceded by a number of pre-Congress activities that will be held on 27 November 2023; information on which will be communicated later. “Your participation in this event will be covered by ITUC-Africa. POLL “While extending to you the assurances of our highest esteem, we look forward to receiving confirmation of your participation at your earliest convenience”.